      "content": "I get where you're coming from, but self-adjusting your warfarin dose can be dangerous. Online anecdotes aren't a substitute for professional medical advice. What works for one person might not work for another, and without careful monitoring, you could slip into a dangerous zone. If you're feeling confident about your health, I suggest discussing a gradual reduction with your doctor. They can provide a safe plan and adjust your dose based on your specific needs. Let's make sure you're not just feeling good, but also staying safe.",
      "source": "target",
